        {
          "text": "To be honest, I feel this is beyond my scope.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_034_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "To be frank, I think this is out of my depth.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_034_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": null
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_035",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "El hotel está cerca del aeropuerto.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "The hotel is near the airport.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The hotel is close to the airport.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "The hotel is situated near the airport.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_035_sideB_2.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[217]**\n\nRemember that [near] doesn't use 'to', while [close] must be followed by [to]. ~Near to the airport~ is a common mistake."
    },
    {
      "cardId": "dummy_036",
      "cardType": "flippable",
      "sideA": "Él se sentó a mi lado en la reunión.",
      "sideB": [
        {
          "text": "He sat next to me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_0.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat beside me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_1.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat right next to me at the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_2.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat by me in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_3.mp3"
        },
        {
          "text": "He sat by my side in the meeting.",
          "audioSrc": "public/data/audio/dummy/dummy_036_sideB_4.mp3"
        }
      ],
      "note": "**[217]**\n\n[Next to] and [beside] indicate being directly adjacent. ~Beside to me~ is incorrect."
